=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_AllpassL_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright mixed sound, with saw_like oscillator character around 51 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 51.1687
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.0938
  harmonic_regularity: 0.9491
  pitch_clarity: 3.8314
  inharmonicity: 0.0338
  type: saw_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -0.0812
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: AllpassL Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/AllpassL.html
// Tags: AllpassL, Classes, reverb
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
// Since the allpass delay has no audible effect as a resonator on
// steady state sound ...

{ AllpassL.ar(WhiteNoise.ar(0.1), 0.01, XLine.kr(0.0001, 0.01, 20), 0.2) }.play;

// ...these examples add the input to the effected sound and compare variants so that you can hear
// the effect of the phase comb:

(
{
    z = WhiteNoise.ar(0.2);
    z + AllpassN.ar(z, 0.01, XLine.kr(0.0001, 0.01, 20), 0.2)
}.play)

(
{
    z = WhiteNoise.ar(0.2);
    z + AllpassL.ar(z, 0.01, XLine.kr(0.0001, 0.01, 20), 0.2)
}.play)

(
{
    z = WhiteNoise.ar(0.2);
    z + AllpassC.ar(z, 0.01, XLine.kr(0.0001, 0.01, 20), 0.2)
}.play)

// used as an echo - doesn't really sound different than Comb,
// but it outputs the input signal immediately (inverted) and the echoes
// are lower in amplitude.
{ AllpassL.ar(Decay.ar(Dust.ar(1, 0.5), 0.2, WhiteNoise.ar), 0.2, 0.2, 3) }.play;
